streams.title: Motorhome
streams.description: There are many ways to apply contextual overrides to a component's styling. That being said, it rarely is easy without rigging up a well-known targeting CSS selector paradigm and then making them accessible for use in interpolations.

streams.title: Motorhomem
streams.description: The styled method works perfectly on all of your own or any third-party component, as long as they attach the passed className prop to a DOM element.

streams.title: !!!Motorhome
streams.description: styled-components solves this use case cleanly via the pattern. Whenever a component is created or wrapped by the styled() factory function, it is also assigned a stable CSS class for use in targeting. This allows for extremely powerful composition patterns without having to fuss around with naming and avoiding selector collisions.
